Vbank, Nigeria’s foremost digital bank powered by VFD Microfinance Bank, on Friday, February 17, 2022, unveiled the redesigned and beautified Thompson Avenue Roundabout located in the heart of Ikoyi, Lagos. The ceremony which was witnessed by top management of the bank led by the Managing Director, Gbenga Omolokun, is said to be one of many to be expected from the bank in the coming months. In his short speech, Omolokun said: ‘’Vbank is committed to bringing the brand closer to its customers. While many know us as a digital bank, we do need to create some offline experience that our customers can relate to”. Why Salim Harps On Support To Local Industries As Panacea To… LASAA Launches e-Sticker Verifier App For Mobile Advert… He added that this roundabout also serves as a strategic investment in infrastructure, and beautificationof the Community. Also commenting on the roundabout, Olufemi Olasope, Brand Manager, Vbank, stated, “Every aspect of the roundabout has been deliberately chosen to appropriately beautify the environs and communicate our brand’s message.” “The greenery signifies the growth we help our customers achieve, while the walkways aim to encourage everyone to interact with us. Our website www.vbank.ng is also boldly positioned at the most visible points of the structure to encourage our customers find out more of the innovative capabilities we offer.” Omolokun expressed that, “We are proud to be positioned in such a prestigious neighborhood and we look forward to coming to more neighborhoods near you as we stay committed to providing excellent service.” Among the striking elements of the roundabout are the iconic V logo which illuminates at night to reflect the radiant colors of the bank; the discretely positioned lighting that is almost invisible during the day but adds the much needed visibility to the structure at night with bold letters that signify the VFD Microfinance bank itself.